The President delivered remarks at the Pentagon on the 16th anniversary of the September 11th terrorist attacks. He expressed condolences to those affected by Hurricane Irma and Hurricane Harvey, and emphasized the unity of the American people in times of need. The President discussed the events of September 11th, honoring the victims and their families. He praised the bravery and sacrifice of the first responders and military personnel who have fought against terrorism since that day. The President reaffirmed America's commitment to defeating terrorism and vowed to protect the country from future attacks. He also paid tribute to the heroes who emerged from the tragedy, such as Pentagon Police Officer Isaac Ho'opi'i, who saved numerous lives during the attack. The President concluded by emphasizing the resilience and strength of the American people and the enduring values of the nation.